shantian_line_sp1900.name: 山田綫千九列車 Shantian Line SP1900 (VSad/WWR Train)
shantian_line_sp1900.description: The Shantian Line SP1900 / SP1920 (also known as SP1900 Modified, Changjin Line SP1900) is a model of train that runs along the Shantian Line. This train has equipped LCDs with MTR Mod Displays. Originally running as part of Connected Transportation's Changjin Line, the train ran the same 6 carriages along with the MLR as part of the West Water Railway (Connected Transportation Division) rolling stock. The rolling stock was then transferred to the Carl Lam server as part of the San Wai Line along with the San Wai Line C1141A (Now known as Shantian Line C1141A, originally named as C1141A modified), before it got transferred to PurpleMTR to serve as the rolling stock for the Shantian Line. Retaining the 6-car configuration from the Changjin Line, there are 4-doors per car, unlike the real life SP1900, which has 5-doors per car, 8-car configuration, that is running on the Tuen Ma Line. The LCD display was updated to show the station name like the Kallos Express SP1900, and was also originally planned to be used for the Shantian Line in Minebahn.

m-3_19_i.name: JR東日本E233系電車 JR East Japan E233 Series by c_toad_gamer
m-3_19_i.description: The E233 series (E233系) is a commuter and suburban electric multiple unit (EMU) train type developed by East Japan Railway Company (JR East) from the earlier E231 series and the E531 series design. The first train was introduced in December 2006 for use on the Chūō Line (Rapid), followed by the E233-1000 series variant in 2007 for use on the Keihin–Tōhoku and Negishi lines, the E233-3000 series outer-suburban variant in December 2007 for use on the Tōkaidō Main Line, and narrow-bodied E233-2000 series variant for Jōban Line and Tokyo Metro Chiyoda Line through services. Further variants were built for use on the Keiyō Line, Yokohama Line, Saikyō Line, and Nambu Line. E233-3000 series:  E233-3000 series: 5- and 10-car sets used on Tōkaidō Main Line, Takasaki Line, and Utsunomiya Line outer-suburban services since March 2008, and on Ueno–Tokyo Line and Shōnan–Shinjuku Line through services since March 2015 This is from wikipedia.org

class_345_elizabeth.name: British Rail Class 345 (Elizabeth Line)
class_345_elizabeth.description: The British Rail Class 345 Aventra is a fleet of electric multiple unit passenger trains built by Bombardier Transportation for use on London's Elizabeth line. Part of Bombardier's Aventra family of trains, the contract for their delivery was awarded as part of the Crossrail project in February 2014. A total of 70 nine-car units each able to carry 1,500 passengers were constructed in Derby between 2015 and 2019, at a cost of over £1 billion. The first unit entered service on 22 June 2017.
